@doclean v0.2
# Machine-readable API spec. Each @endpoint block is one API call.
@api Linode API
@base https://api.linode.com/v4
@version 4.145.0
@auth OAuth2 | Bearer bearer
@endpoints 350
@toc Account View, Account Update, Account Cancel, Credit Card Add/Edit, Entity Transfers List, Entity Transfer Create, Entity Transfer Cancel, Entity Transfer View, Entity Transfer Accept, Events List, Event View, Event Mark as Read, Event Mark as Seen, Invoices List, Invoice View, Invoice Items List, User Logins List All, Login View, Maintenance List, Notifications List, OAuth Clients List, OAuth Client Create, OAuth Client Delete, OAuth Client View, OAuth Client Update, OAuth Client Secret Reset, OAuth Client Thumbnail View, OAuth Client Thumbnail Update, Payment Methods List, Payment Method Add, Payment Method Delete, Payment Method View, Payment Method Make Default, Payments List, Payment Make, PayPal Payment Stage, Staged/Approved PayPal Payment Execute, Payment View, Promo Credit Add, Service Transfers List, Service Transfer Create, Service Transfer Cancel, Service Transfer View, Service Transfer Accept, Account Settings View, Account Settings Update, Linode Managed Enable, Network Utilization View, Users List, User Create, User Delete, User View, User Update, User's Grants View, User's Grants Update, Managed Database Engines List, Managed Database Engine View, Managed Databases List All, Managed MongoDB Databases List, Managed MongoDB Database Delete, Managed MongoDB Database View, Managed MongoDB Database Update, Managed MongoDB Database Backups List, Managed MongoDB Database Backup Snapshot Create, Managed MongoDB Database Backup Delete, Managed MongoDB Database Backup View, Managed MongoDB Database Backup Restore, Managed MongoDB Database Credentials View, Managed MongoDB Database Credentials Reset, Managed MongoDB Database Patch, Managed MongoDB Database SSL Certificate View, Managed MySQL Databases List, Managed MySQL Database Create, Managed MySQL Database Delete, Managed MySQL Database View, Managed MySQL Database Update, Managed MySQL Database Backups List, Managed MySQL Database Backup Snapshot Create, Managed MySQL Database Backup Delete, Managed MySQL Database Backup View, Managed MySQL Database Backup Restore, Managed MySQL Database Credentials View, Managed MySQL Database Credentials Reset, Managed MySQL Database Patch, Managed MySQL Database SSL Certificate View, Managed PostgreSQL Databases List, Managed PostgreSQL Database Create, Managed PostgreSQL Database Delete, Managed PostgreSQL Database View, Managed PostgreSQL Database Update, Managed PostgreSQL Database Backups List, Managed PostgreSQL Database Backup Snapshot Create, Managed PostgreSQL Database Backup Delete, Managed PostgreSQL Database Backup View, Managed PostgreSQL Database Backup Restore, Managed PostgreSQL Database Credentials View, Managed PostgreSQL Database Credentials Reset, Managed PostgreSQL Database Patch, Managed PostgreSQL Database SSL Certificate View, Managed Database Types List, Managed Database Type View, Domains List, Domain Create, Domain Import, Domain Delete, Domain View, Domain Update, Domain Clone, Domain Records List, Domain Record Create, Domain Record Delete, Domain Record View, Domain Record Update, Domain Zone File View, Images List, Image Create, Image Upload, Image Delete, Image View, Image Update, Linodes List, Linode Create, Linode Delete, Linode View, Linode Update, Backups List, Snapshot Create, Backups Cancel, Backups Enable, Backup View, Backup Restore, Linode Boot, Linode Clone, Configuration Profiles List, Configuration Profile Create, Configuration Profile Delete, Configuration Profile View, Configuration Profile Update, Disks List, Disk Create, Disk Delete, Disk View, Disk Update, Disk Clone, Disk Root Password Reset, Disk Resize, Firewalls List, Networking Information List, IPv4 Address Allocate, IPv4 Address Delete, IP Address View, IP Address Update, DC Migration/Pending Host Migration Initiate, Linode Upgrade, Linode NodeBalancers View, Linode Root Password Reset, Linode Reboot, Linode Rebuild, Linode Boot into Rescue Mode, Linode Resize, Linode Shut Down, Linode Statistics View, Statistics View (year/month), Network Transfer View, Network Transfer View (year/month), Linode's Volumes List, Kernels List, Kernel View, StackScripts List, StackScript Create, StackScript Delete, StackScript View, StackScript Update, Types List, Type View, Kubernetes Clusters List, Kubernetes Cluster Create, Kubernetes Cluster Delete, Kubernetes Cluster View, Kubernetes Cluster Update, Kubernetes API Endpoints List, Kubernetes Cluster Dashboard URL View, Kubeconfig Delete, Kubeconfig View, Node Delete, Node View, Node Recycle, Node Pools List, Node Pool Create, Node Pool Delete, Node Pool View, Node Pool Update, Node Pool Recycle, Cluster Nodes Recycle, Kubernetes Cluster Regenerate, Service Token Delete, Kubernetes Versions List, Kubernetes Version View, Longview Clients List, Longview Client Create, Longview Client Delete, Longview Client View, Longview Client Update, Longview Plan View, Longview Plan Update, Longview Subscriptions List, Longview Subscription View, Managed Contacts List, Managed Contact Create, Managed Contact Delete, Managed Contact View, Managed Contact Update, Managed Credentials List, Managed Credential Create, Managed SSH Key View, Managed Credential View, Managed Credential Update, Managed Credential Delete, Managed Credential Username and Password Update, Managed Issues List, Managed Issue View, Managed Linode Settings List, Linode's Managed Settings View, Linode's Managed Settings Update, Managed Services List, Managed Service Create, Managed Service Delete, Managed Service View, Managed Service Update, Managed Service Disable, Managed Service Enable, Managed Stats List, Firewalls List, Firewall Create, Firewall Delete, Firewall View, Firewall Update, Firewall Devices List, Firewall Device Create, Firewall Device Delete, Firewall Device View, Firewall Rules List, Firewall Rules Update, IP Addresses List, IP Address Allocate, IP Addresses Assign, IP Addresses Share, IP Address View, IP Address RDNS Update, Linodes Assign IPv4s, IPv4 Sharing Configure, IPv6 Pools List, IPv6 Ranges List, IPv6 Range Create, IPv6 Range Delete, IPv6 Range View, VLANs List, NodeBalancers List, NodeBalancer Create, NodeBalancer Delete, NodeBalancer View, NodeBalancer Update, Configs List, Config Create, Config Delete, Config View, Config Update, Nodes List, Node Create, Node Delete, Node View, Node Update, Config Rebuild, NodeBalancer Statistics View, Object Storage Buckets List, Object Storage Bucket Create, Object Storage Buckets in Cluster List, Object Storage Bucket Remove, Object Storage Bucket View, Object Storage Bucket Access Modify, Object Storage Bucket Access Update, Object Storage Object ACL Config View, Object Storage Object ACL Config Update, Object Storage Bucket Contents List, Object Storage Object URL Create, Object Storage TLS/SSL Cert Delete, Object Storage TLS/SSL Cert View, Object Storage TLS/SSL Cert Upload, Object Storage Cancel, Clusters List, Cluster View, Object Storage Keys List, Object Storage Key Create, Object Storage Key Revoke, Object Storage Key View, Object Storage Key Update, Object Storage Transfer View, Profile View, Profile Update, Authorized Apps List, App Access Revoke, Authorized App View, Trusted Devices List, Trusted Device Revoke, Trusted Device View, Grants List, Logins List, Login View, Phone Number Delete, Phone Number Verification Code Send, Phone Number Verify, User Preferences View, User Preferences Update, Security Questions List, Security Questions Answer, SSH Keys List, SSH Key Add, SSH Key Delete, SSH Key View, SSH Key Update, Two Factor Authentication Disable, Two Factor Secret Create, Two Factor Authentication Confirm/Enable, Personal Access Tokens List, Personal Access Token Create, Personal Access Token Revoke, Personal Access Token View, Personal Access Token Update, Regions List, Region View, Support Tickets List, Support Ticket Open, Support Ticket View, Support Ticket Attachment Create, Support Ticket Close, Replies List, Reply Create, Tags List, New Tag Create, Tag Delete, Tagged Objects List, Volumes List, Volume Create, Volume Delete, Volume View, Volume Update, Volume Attach, Volume Clone, Volume Detach, Volume Resize

@endpoint GET /account
@desc Account View
@returns(200) {active_promotions: [map], active_since: str(date-time), address_1: str, address_2: str, balance: num, balance_uninvoiced: num, billing_source: str, capabilities: [str], city: str, company: str, country: str, credit_card: map{expiry: str, last_four: str}, email: str, euuid: str(uuid), first_name: str, last_name: str, phone: str, state: str, tax_id: str, zip: str} # Returns a single Account object.

@endpoint PUT /account
@desc Account Update
@optional {active_promotions: [map], active_since: str(date-time) # The datetime of when the account was activated., address_1: str # First line of this Account's billing address., address_2: str # Second line of this Account's billing address., balance: num # This Account's balance, in US dollars., balance_uninvoiced: num # This Account's current estimated invoice in US dollars. This is not your final invoice balance. Transfer charges are not included in the estimate., billing_source: str(akamai/linode) # The source of service charges for this Account, as determined by its relationship with Akamai. Accounts that are associated with Akamai-specific customers return a value of `akamai`. All other Accounts return a value of `linode`., capabilities: [str] # A list of capabilities your account supports., city: str # The city for this Account's billing address., company: str # The company name associated with this Account., country: str # The two-letter ISO 3166 country code of this Account's billing address., credit_card: map # Credit Card information associated with this Account., email: str # The email address of the person associated with this Account., euuid: str(uuid) # An external unique identifier for this account., first_name: str # The first name of the person associated with this Account., last_name: str # The last name of the person associated with this Account., phone: str # The phone number associated with this Account., state: str # If billing address is in the United States (US) or Canada (CA), only the two-letter ISO 3166 State or Province code are accepted. If entering a US military address, state abbreviations (AA, AE, AP) should be entered. If the address is outside the US or CA, this is the Province associated with the Account's billing address., tax_id: str # The tax identification number associated with this Account, for tax calculations in some countries. If you do not live in a country that collects tax, this should be an empty string (`""`)., zip: str # The zip code of this Account's billing address. The following restrictions apply:  - May only consist of letters, numbers, spaces, and hyphens. - Must not contain more than 9 letter or number characters.}
@returns(200) {active_promotions: [map], active_since: str(date-time), address_1: str, address_2: str, balance: num, balance_uninvoiced: num, billing_source: str, capabilities: [str], city: str, company: str, country: str, credit_card: map{expiry: str, last_four: str}, email: str, euuid: str(uuid), first_name: str, last_name: str, phone: str, state: str, tax_id: str, zip: str} # The updated Account.

@endpoint POST /account/cancel
@desc Account Cancel
@optional {comments: str # Any reason for cancelling the account, and any other comments you might have about your Linode service.}
@returns(200) {survey_link: str} # Account cancelled
@errors {409: Could not charge the credit card on file}

@endpoint POST /account/credit-card
@desc Credit Card Add/Edit
@required {card_number: str(digits) # Your credit card number. No spaces or dashes allowed., cvv: str(digits) # CVV (Card Verification Value) of the credit card, typically found on the back of the card., expiry_month: int # A value from 1-12 representing the expiration month of your credit card.    * 1 = January   * 2 = February   * 3 = March   * Etc., expiry_year: int # A four-digit integer representing the expiration year of your credit card.  The combination of `expiry_month` and `expiry_year` must result in a month/year combination of the current month or in the future. An expiration date set in the past is invalid.}
@returns(200) Credit Card updated.

@endpoint GET /account/entity-transfers
@desc Entity Transfers List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) Returns a paginated list of Entity Transfer objects containing the details of all transfers that have been created and accepted by this account.


@endpoint POST /account/entity-transfers
@desc Entity Transfer Create
@required {entities: map # A collection of the entities to include in this transfer request, separated by type.}
@returns(200) {created: str(date-time), entities: map{linodes: [int]}, expiry: str(date-time), is_sender: bool, status: str, token: str(uuid), updated: str(date-time)} # Returns an Entity Transfer object for the request.


@endpoint DELETE /account/entity-transfers/{token}
@desc Entity Transfer Cancel
@returns(200) Entity Transfer cancelled.


@endpoint GET /account/entity-transfers/{token}
@desc Entity Transfer View
@returns(200) {created: str(date-time), entities: map{linodes: [int]}, expiry: str(date-time), is_sender: bool, status: str, token: str(uuid), updated: str(date-time)} # Returns an Entity Transfer object containing the details of the transfer for the specified token.


@endpoint POST /account/entity-transfers/{token}/accept
@desc Entity Transfer Accept
@returns(200) Entity Transfer accepted.


@endpoint GET /account/events
@desc Events List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # Returns a paginated lists of Event objects from the last 90 days.


@endpoint GET /account/events/{eventId}
@desc Event View
@returns(200) {action: str, created: str(date-time), duration: num, entity: map{id: int, label: str, type: str, url: str}, id: int, message: str?, percent_complete: int, rate: str, read: bool, secondary_entity: map{id: str, label: str, type: str, url: str}, seen: bool, status: str, time_remaining: str?, username: str?} # An Event object

@endpoint POST /account/events/{eventId}/read
@desc Event Mark as Read
@returns(200) Event read.

@endpoint POST /account/events/{eventId}/seen
@desc Event Mark as Seen
@returns(200) Events seen.

@endpoint GET /account/invoices
@desc Invoices List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # Returns a paginated list of Invoice objects.

@endpoint GET /account/invoices/{invoiceId}
@desc Invoice View
@returns(200) {date: str(date-time), id: int, label: str, subtotal: num, tax: num, tax_summary: [map], total: num} # An Invoice object

@endpoint GET /account/invoices/{invoiceId}/items
@desc Invoice Items List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # A paginated list of InvoiceItem objects

@endpoint GET /account/logins
@desc User Logins List All
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # A collection of successful logins for all users on the account during the last 90 days.


@endpoint GET /account/logins/{loginId}
@desc Login View
@returns(200) {datetime: str(date-time), id: int, ip: str(ip), restricted: bool, username: str} # The requested login object.

@endpoint GET /account/maintenance
@desc Maintenance List
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # Returns a paginated list of Maintenance objects.

@endpoint GET /account/notifications
@desc Notifications List
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # Returns a paginated list of Notification objects.

@endpoint GET /account/oauth-clients
@desc OAuth Clients List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # A paginated list of OAuth Clients.

@endpoint POST /account/oauth-clients
@desc OAuth Client Create
@returns(200) {id: str, label: str, public: bool, redirect_uri: str(url), secret: str, status: str, thumbnail_url: str(url)?} # Client created successfully.

@endpoint DELETE /account/oauth-clients/{clientId}
@desc OAuth Client Delete
@returns(200) Client deleted successfully.

@endpoint GET /account/oauth-clients/{clientId}
@desc OAuth Client View
@returns(200) {id: str, label: str, public: bool, redirect_uri: str(url), secret: str, status: str, thumbnail_url: str(url)?} # Information about the requested client.

@endpoint PUT /account/oauth-clients/{clientId}
@desc OAuth Client Update
@optional {id: str # The OAuth Client ID.  This is used to identify the client, and is a publicly-known value (it is not a secret)., label: str # The name of this application.  This will be presented to users when they are asked to grant it access to their Account., public: bool=False # If this is a public or private OAuth Client.  Public clients have a slightly different authentication workflow than private clients.  See the <a target="_top" href="https://oauth.net/2/">OAuth spec</a> for more details., redirect_uri: str(url) # The location a successful log in from <a target="_top" href="https://login.linode.com">https://login.linode.com</a> should be redirected to for this client.  The receiver of this redirect should be ready to accept an OAuth exchange code and finish the OAuth exchange., secret: str # The OAuth Client secret, used in the OAuth exchange.  This is returned as `<REDACTED>` except when an OAuth Client is created or its secret is reset.  This is a secret, and should not be shared or disclosed publicly., status: str(active/disabled/suspended) # The status of this application.  `active` by default., thumbnail_url: str(url) # The URL where this client's thumbnail may be viewed, or `null` if this client does not have a thumbnail set.}
@returns(200) {id: str, label: str, public: bool, redirect_uri: str(url), secret: str, status: str, thumbnail_url: str(url)?} # Client updated successfully.

@endpoint POST /account/oauth-clients/{clientId}/reset-secret
@desc OAuth Client Secret Reset
@returns(200) {id: str, label: str, public: bool, redirect_uri: str(url), secret: str, status: str, thumbnail_url: str(url)?} # Client secret reset successfully.

@endpoint GET /account/oauth-clients/{clientId}/thumbnail
@desc OAuth Client Thumbnail View
@returns(200) The client's thumbnail.

@endpoint PUT /account/oauth-clients/{clientId}/thumbnail
@desc OAuth Client Thumbnail Update
@returns(200) Thumbnail updated successfully.

@endpoint GET /account/payment-methods
@desc Payment Methods List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # Returns a paginated list of Payment Method objects.

@endpoint POST /account/payment-methods
@desc Payment Method Add
@required {data: map # An object representing the credit card information you have on file with Linode to make Payments against your Account., is_default: bool # Whether this Payment Method is the default method for automatically processing service charges., type: str # The type of Payment Method.  Alternative Payment Methods including Google Pay and PayPal can be added using the Cloud Manager. See the [Manage Payment Methods](/docs/products/platform/billing/guides/payment-methods/) guide for details and instructions.}
@returns(200) Payment Method added.

@endpoint DELETE /account/payment-methods/{paymentMethodId}
@desc Payment Method Delete
@returns(200) Payment Method deactivated.

@endpoint GET /account/payment-methods/{paymentMethodId}
@desc Payment Method View
@returns(200) {created: str(date-time), data: any, id: int, is_default: bool, type: str} # Returns a Payment Method Object.

@endpoint POST /account/payment-methods/{paymentMethodId}/make-default
@desc Payment Method Make Default
@returns(200) Payment Method successfully set as the default method.

@endpoint GET /account/payments
@desc Payments List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # Returns a paginated list of Payment objects.

@endpoint POST /account/payments
@desc Payment Make
@required {usd: str # The amount in US Dollars of the Payment.  * Can begin with or without `$`. * Commas (`,`) are not accepted. * Must end with a decimal expression, such as `.00` or `.99`. * Minimum: `$5.00` or the Account balance, whichever is lower. * Maximum: `$2000.00` or the Account balance up to `$50000.00`, whichever is greater.}
@optional {cvv: str # CVV (Card Verification Value) of the credit card to be used for the Payment. Required if paying by credit card., payment_method_id: int # The ID of the Payment Method to apply to the Payment.}
@returns(200) {date: str(date-time), id: int, usd: int} # Payment submitted successfully.
@returns(202) {warnings: [map]} # Accepted with warning.

A warnings array is included with the standard 200 response body.


@endpoint POST /account/payments/paypal
@desc PayPal Payment Stage
@required {cancel_url: str # The URL to have PayPal redirect to when Payment is cancelled., redirect_url: str # The URL to have PayPal redirect to when Payment is approved., usd: str # The payment amount in USD. Minimum accepted value of $5 USD. Maximum accepted value of $500 USD or credit card payment limit; whichever value is highest. PayPal's maximum transaction limit is $10,000 USD.}
@returns(200) {checkout_token: str, payment_id: str} # PayPal Payment staged.
@returns(299) {warnings: [map]} # Request successful. This endpoint is deprecated and may be removed in a future release.

A warnings array is included with the standard 200 response body.


@endpoint POST /account/payments/paypal/execute
@desc Staged/Approved PayPal Payment Execute
@required {payer_id: str # The PayerID returned by PayPal during the transaction authorization process., payment_id: str # The PaymentID returned from [POST /account/payments/paypal](/docs/api/account/#paypal-payment-stage) that has been approved with PayPal.}
@returns(200) PayPal Payment executed.
@returns(202) {warnings: [map]} # Accepted with warning.

A warnings array is included with the standard 200 response body.

@returns(299) {warnings: [map]} # Request successful. This endpoint is deprecated and may be removed in a future release.

A warnings array is included with the standard 200 response body.


@endpoint GET /account/payments/{paymentId}
@desc Payment View
@returns(200) {date: str(date-time), id: int, usd: int} # A Payment object.

@endpoint POST /account/promo-codes
@desc Promo Credit Add
@required {promo_code: str # The Promo Code.}
@returns(200) {credit_monthly_cap: str, credit_remaining: str, description: str, expire_dt: str, image_url: str, service_type: str, summary: str, this_month_credit_remaining: str} # Promo Credit successfully added.


@endpoint GET /account/service-transfers
@desc Service Transfers List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # Returns a paginated list of Service Transfer objects containing the details of all transfers that have been created and accepted by this account.


@endpoint POST /account/service-transfers
@desc Service Transfer Create
@required {entities: map # A collection of the services to include in this transfer request, separated by type.}
@returns(200) {created: str(date-time), entities: map{linodes: [int]}, expiry: str(date-time), is_sender: bool, status: str, token: str(uuid), updated: str(date-time)} # Returns a Service Transfer object for the request.


@endpoint DELETE /account/service-transfers/{token}
@desc Service Transfer Cancel
@returns(200) Service Transfer cancelled.


@endpoint GET /account/service-transfers/{token}
@desc Service Transfer View
@returns(200) {created: str(date-time), entities: map{linodes: [int]}, expiry: str(date-time), is_sender: bool, status: str, token: str(uuid), updated: str(date-time)} # Returns a Service Transfer object containing the details of the transfer for the specified token.


@endpoint POST /account/service-transfers/{token}/accept
@desc Service Transfer Accept
@returns(200) Service Transfer accepted.


@endpoint GET /account/settings
@desc Account Settings View
@returns(200) {backups_enabled: bool, longview_subscription: str, managed: bool, network_helper: bool, object_storage: str} # Returns a single Account settings object.

@endpoint PUT /account/settings
@desc Account Settings Update
@optional {backups_enabled: bool # Account-wide backups default.  If `true`, all Linodes created will automatically be enrolled in the Backups service.  If `false`, Linodes will not be enrolled by default, but may still be enrolled on creation or later., longview_subscription: str # The Longview Pro tier you are currently subscribed to. The value must be a [Longview Subscription](/docs/api/longview/#longview-subscriptions-list) ID or `null` for Longview Free., managed: bool # Our 24/7 incident response service. This robust, multi-homed monitoring system distributes monitoring checks to ensure that your servers remain online and available at all times. Linode Managed can monitor any service or software stack reachable over TCP or HTTP. Once you add a service to Linode Managed, we'll monitor it for connectivity, response, and total request time., network_helper: bool # Enables network helper across all users by default for new Linodes and Linode Configs., object_storage: str(disabled/suspended/active)=disabled # A string describing the status of this account's Object Storage service enrollment.}
@returns(200) {backups_enabled: bool, longview_subscription: str, managed: bool, network_helper: bool, object_storage: str} # The updated Account settings.

@endpoint POST /account/settings/managed-enable
@desc Linode Managed Enable
@returns(200) Managed services enabled for account.

@endpoint GET /account/transfer
@desc Network Utilization View
@returns(200) {billable: int, quota: int, used: int} # Returns a single Transfer object.

@endpoint GET /account/users
@desc Users List
@optional {page: int=1 # The page of a collection to return., page_size: int=100 # The number of items to return per page.}
@returns(200) {data: [map], page: int, pages: int, results: int} # A paginated list of Users.

@endpoint POST /account/users
@desc User Create
@returns(200) {email: str(email), restricted: bool, ssh_keys: [str], tfa_enabled: bool, username: str} # New User created successfully.

@endpoint DELETE /account/users/{username}
@desc User Delete
@returns(200) User deleted successfully.

@endpoint GET /account/users/{username}
@desc User View
@returns(200) {email: str(email), restricted: bool, ssh_keys: [str], tfa_enabled: bool, username: str} # The requested User object

@endpoint PUT /account/users/{username}
@desc User Update
@optional {email: str(email) # The email address for the User. Linode sends emails to this address for account management communications. May be used for other communications as configured., restricted: bool # If true, the User must be granted access to perform actions or access entities on this Account. See User Grants View ([GET /account/users/{username}/grants](/docs/api/account/#users-grants-view)) for details on how to configure grants for a restricted User., ssh_keys: [str] # A list of SSH Key labels added by this User.  Users can add keys with the SSH Key Add ([POST /profile/sshkeys](/docs/api/profile/#ssh-key-add)) command.  These keys are deployed when this User is included in the `authorized_users` field of the following requests: - Linode Create ([POST /linode/instances](/docs/api/linode-instances/#linode-create)) - Linode Rebuild ([POST /linode/instances/{linodeId}/rebuild](/docs/api/linode-instances/#linode-rebuild)) - Disk Create ([POST /linode/instances/{linodeId}/disks](/docs/api/linode-instances/#disk-create)), tfa_enabled: bool # A boolean value indicating if the User has Two Factor Authentication (TFA) enabled. See the Create Two Factor Secret ([POST /profile/tfa-enable](/docs/api/profile/#two-factor-secret-create)) endpoint to enable TFA., username: str # The User's username. This is used for logging in, and may also be displayed alongside actions the User performs (for example, in Events or public StackScripts).}
@returns(200) {email: str(email), restricted: bool, ssh_keys: [str], tfa_enabled: bool, username: str} # User updated successfully.

@endpoint GET /account/users/{username}/grants
@desc User's Grants View
@returns(200) {database: [map], domain: [map], global: map{account_access: str?, add_databases: bool, add_domains: bool, add_firewalls: bool, add_images: bool, add_linodes: bool, add_longview: bool, add_nodebalancers: bool, add_stackscripts: bool, add_volumes: bool, cancel_account: bool, longview_subscription: bool}, image: [map], linode: [map], longview: [map], nodebalancer: [map], stackscript: [map], volume: [map]} # The User's grants.
@returns(204) This is an unrestricted User, and therefore has no grants to return. This User may access everything on the Account and perform all actions.


@endpoint PUT /account/users/{username}/grants
@desc User's Grants Update
@optional {database: [map] # The grants this User has for each Database that is owned by this Account., domain: [map] # The grants this User has for each Domain that is owned by this Account., global: map # A structure containing the Account-level grants a User has., image: [map] # The grants this User has for each Image that is owned by this Account., linode: [map] # The grants this User has for each Linode that is owned by this Account., longview: [map] # The grants this User has for each Longview Client that is owned by this Account., nodebalancer: [map] # The grants this User has for each NodeBalancer that is owned by this Account., stackscript: [map] # The grants this User has for each StackScript that is owned by this Account., volume: [map] # The grants this User has for each Block Storage Volume that is owned by this Account.}
